http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 26 Jan 2013
Source: OIE, WAHID (World Animal Health Information Database), weekly disease information 2013; 26(5) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=12929


Venezuelan equine encephalomyelitis, Belize
-------------------------------------------
Information received on 26 Jan 2013 from Dr Miguel Angel Depaz, Director of Animal Health, Animal Health Department, Belize Agricultural Health Authority (BAHA), Belmopan, Belize

Summary:
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 29 Oct 2012
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 24 Jan 2013
Report date: 25 Jan 2013
Date submitted to OIE: 26 Jan 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 19 Nov 2010
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: Venezuelan equine encephalomyelitis [VEE] virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1 (EQ01/13): Little Belize, Corozal South East, Little Belize, Corozal
Date of start of the outbreak: 29 Oct 2012
Outbreak status: resolved (29 Nov 2012)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 16 / 4 / 3 / 0 / 0
Affected population: draught horses in Mennonite community in deeply forested area in the North of Belize.

Outbreak 2 (EQ02/13): Cayo, Cayo Northeast, Bullet Tree, Cayo
Date of start of the outbreak: 11 Jan 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: village
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 3 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: pleasure horse kept at home in a village.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Equidae / 19 / 5 / 3 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics:
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 26.32 percent / 15.79 percent / 60.00 percent / 15.79 percent
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: horses located in areas where outbreaks have occurred in the past.

Control measures
Measures applied: control of arthropods, quarantine, no vaccination, treatment of affected animals (treatment for secondary infections)
Measures to be applied: vaccination in response to the outbreak(s)

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
National Veterinary Services Laboratory, United States of America (OIE's Reference Laboratory) / Equidae / IgM-capture ELISA / 24/01/2013 / Positive

Future reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

Map of outbreak locations [The 2 loci are marked on the OIE map at the source URL above. - Mod.MHJ]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Belize reported VEE outbreaks to OIE in 2009 and 2010. Guatemala had sporadic reports for 2009 and 2010; and Mexico reported singular outbreaks in Tabasco and Veracruz in 2011, not before or since. ProMED-mail carried them for Belize in 2010 and 2009 and for Mexico in 2011; none for Guatemala. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1AYt.]
